def data_research(dataset):
    
    display(dataset.head())
    display(dataset.tail())
    print()
    
    display(HTML('<h3>   </h3><br>'))
    print(dataset.info())
    
    if dataset.isna().sum().any():
    
        display(HTML('<br><h3>  </h3><br>'))
        print(dataset.isna().sum())
    
        display(HTML('<br><h3>  </h3><br>'))
        display(HTML(f'<b>  : </b>'\
                     f'{round((dataset.isna().sum().sum() / (dataset.shape[0] * dataset.shape[1]) * 100), 1)}%<br>'))
        
        
        display(HTML('<b>  : </b>'))
        display(pd.DataFrame(dataset.isna().mean()*100).style.set_precision(1).background_gradient('coolwarm'))
    
    else:
        pass
    
    if len(int_col(dataset)) != 0:

        display(HTML('<br><h3> </h3>'))
        display(dataset.describe())
        
        display(HTML('<br><h3>     </h3><br>'))
        axes = dataset.hist(figsize=(10, 10), xlabelsize=10, ylabelsize=10)

        #   
        for ax in axes.flatten():
            ax.set_xlabel(ax.get_title(), fontsize=12)
            ax.set_ylabel(' ', fontsize=12)

        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
   
    else:
        pass

def quantitative_plot(data, column, step_size):
    
    #         
    #   ,      
    min_value = np.floor(data[column].min() / step_size) * step_size
    max_value = np.ceil(data[column].max() / step_size) * step_size + step_size * 1.5
    
    data.hist(column=column, 
              bins=np.arange(min_value, max_value, step_size), 
              figsize=(10, 5));
    
    plt.ylabel(' ')

def categorical_plot(data, column):
    data[column].sort_values()\
                .value_counts()\
                .sort_index()\
                .plot(kind='pie', 
                      figsize=(8, 8), 
                      autopct='%1.1f%%', 
                      colors=['lightskyblue', 'orchid', 'orange', 'yellowgreen']);

#       .  
def residuals_plot(pred):
    #  
    residuals = y_test - pred

    #   
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(10,5))
    axes[0].hist(residuals)
    axes[0].set_title('  ')
    axes[0].set_xlabel('')
    axes[0].grid(True)  

    #  
    axes[1].scatter(residuals, pred)
    axes[1].set_title(' ')
    axes[1].set_xlabel('')
    axes[1].set_ylabel(' ')
    axes[1].grid(True)
    
    plt.show()

#     accuracy, precision  recall.
def apr_metrics(pred):
    print('Accuracy =', accuracy_score(y_test, pred))
    print('Precision =', precision_score(y_test, pred, pos_label=''))
    print('Recall =', recall_score(y_test, pred, pos_label=''))

#     .
def cm_plot(true, pred):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(true, pred), annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues_r', 
                xticklabels=['', ''], yticklabels=['', ''])
    plt.xlabel(' ')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.title(' ')
    plt.show()

categorical_corr = main_data[main_data.columns[1:]]\
    .phik_matrix(interval_cols=int_col(main_data))\
    .drop(int_col(main_data)[1:], axis=0)

#     
results = {}

#   
for column in main_data.columns[1:]:
    
    #     
    results[column] = {'': [], '': [], '': [], '': []}
    
    # ,      
    if column in quantitative_corr.columns:
        #    quantitative_corr  categorical_corr
        correlations = pd.concat([quantitative_corr[column], categorical_corr[column]])
    else:
        #       
        correlations = categorical_corr.loc[column]
    
    #    
    correlations = correlations.sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    #      
    if column in correlations:
        correlations = correlations.drop(column)
    
    #    
    for column2, corr_result in correlations.items():
        if corr_result >= 0.7:
            results[column][''].append(f'{column2} ({round(corr_result, 2)})')
        elif corr_result >= 0.5:
            results[column][''].append(f'{column2} ({round(corr_result, 2)})')
        elif corr_result >= 0.3:
            results[column][''].append(f'{column2} ({round(corr_result, 2)})')
        elif corr_result >= 0.1:
            results[column][''].append(f'{column2} ({round(corr_result, 2)})')

#  
for column, correlations in results.items():
    display(HTML(f'<br><b>{column}:</b>'))
    for category, corr_list in correlations.items():
        # ,   
        if len(corr_list) > 0:
            print(f'{category}: {", ".join(corr_list)}')
